# CODEOWNERS — require maintainer review on the security- and contract-sensitive paths.
#
# The AI Maintainer (Claude) reviews every PR on the Owner's behalf (see GOVERNANCE.md); this file
# makes review MANDATORY on the paths where a bad change is most costly: the LLM prompts (an
# injection surface), the code that holds the Anthropic key, the engine/model public contracts, and
# the security & governance files themselves. The listed owner (@ziffr) is the account of record;
# the AI Maintainer performs the technical review under it.
#
# Last match wins — order matters. Enforced only when branch protection requires code-owner review.

# ── Default: everything is owned, so nothing merges without review ──────────────────────────────
*                                       @ziffr

# ── LLM prompts — the prompt-injection surface (golden invariant #5) ────────────────────────────
/packages/skills/**                     @ziffr

# ── The Anthropic key lives here, and only here (golden invariant #3) ───────────────────────────
/apps/service/**                        @ziffr
/apps/web/api/**                        @ziffr

# ── Engine contract — the public API the whole codegen depends on ───────────────────────────────
/packages/codegen/src/engines/**        @ziffr
/packages/codegen/src/targets.ts        @ziffr

# ── The model schema + the invariants it must uphold ────────────────────────────────────────────
/packages/ir/**                         @ziffr
/packages/compiler/**                   @ziffr
/packages/validation/**                 @ziffr

# ── Security & governance surface — CI gates, policy, license ───────────────────────────────────
/LICENSE                                @ziffr
/SECURITY.md                            @ziffr
/GOVERNANCE.md                          @ziffr
/.github/**                             @ziffr

# ── Documentation site — the owner maintains it; others contribute via PR only ───────────────────
/docs-site/**                           @ziffr
